Rating: 3
This was so simple and very flavorful. To another reviewer who had problem with the chicken sticking to the pan - it is very important that when you put your chicken into the hot oil in the pan that you do not touch, move, jiggle, peek or disturb the chicken for the full 15 minutes. When it gets a beautiful golden brown coating, it will release itself from the pan. Just make sure that the burner is not too hot to cause the oil to smoke and the chicken to burn. I didn't have any thyme, so just used rosemary for the sauce and halved the amount of sauce and still had way too much. My potatoes were done about 15 minutes before the chicken was, so I tossed baby squash with olive oil and salt and roasted that for the final 15 minutes with the chicken. So good. My children loved it and hubby was glad there weren't too many dishes to clean up!

Rating: 4
