Rating: 3
This recipe was GREAT!! I did not have shallots so I used finely chopped onions which worked just fine. I had some left over roasted garlic cloves which I added and let simmer with the sauce - that turned out to be the best part. The garlic gave it a very nice flavour. I agree with the other reviewers about the time - it took 45 minutes to get to the right consistency. As suggested by another reviewer, I marinated the chicken overnight in balsamic vinegar, garlic and a dash of worchester sauce and then grilled the chicken. I much prefer grilled chicken and you save yourself 6 tbsp of oil (I used skinless chicken as well). My last usggestion is that you do not need to add any extra salt to the chicken or sauce as it is already quite salty even with the low salt broth. The potatoes were great and I've already had a request to make them again this week. This recipe is definately a keeper.

