Rating: 3
I made this recipe for a big family dinner party. I like to make as much of the meal in advance and adapted this recipe. Instead of roasting the chicken, I used breast tenders. I find that my family don't like huge chunks of chicken breast especially the oversized ones that seem to be the norm when you buy supermarket packs of boneless breasts. I marinated the tenders in balsamic vinegar, crushed garlic, salt and pepper for a few hours. I then lightly grilled the tenders on the barbecue ensuring they did not dry out. I had made the sauce ahead of time following tips about using low salt broth and doubled the amount of balsamic vinegar.I poured the premade sauce over the tenders and baked it all in the sauce for about 20 minutes.It was outstanding. Everybody raved about it and came back for more. I will definitely be adding this to my list of great entertaining meals.

